Sentencas: The proton conduction behavior and electrochemical performance of PrBaFe2O5+delta (PBF) are firstly studied for use as promising anode materials in symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (PCFCs).
Titulo: PrBaFe2O5+δ promising electrode for redox-stable symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study focuses on the investigation of protonic defect formation in PBF and its properties as an electrode, including its chemical stability, electrochemical performance and redox stability.
Titulo: PrBaFe2O5+δ promising electrode for redox-stable symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PBF is found to have proton conductivity at intermediate temperatures, which contributes to improved hydrogen oxidation reaction and water formation reaction at the anode and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: PrBaFe2O5+δ promising electrode for redox-stable symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Hence, the symmetrical PCFC exhibits a peak power density of 301 mW.cm(-2) and total resistance of 0.77 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C. Further, it shows excellent redox-cycle stability upon cycling between fuel and air under a current load.
Titulo: PrBaFe2O5+δ promising electrode for redox-stable symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical analysis and redox cycling tests of the PBF anode demonstrate that PBF is an attractive candidate for alternative material for symmetrical PCFCs.
Titulo: PrBaFe2O5+δ promising electrode for redox-stable symmetrical proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
